We are seeking Computer Network Professionals for our Cairns office.

Salary commensurate with skills and experience ($76-$105k)

** The Team & The Place **

TJ Microsystems is a locally owned and operated company with over 25 years in
business and 20 staff with service locations in Cairns, Townsville and
Brisbane. We are one of the largest Managed IT Providers in North Queensland,
specialising in delivering high quality IT services to our diverse client
base. With a great work and social culture and a supportive team we work hard
and we play hard. From our staff camping and water skiing trips to our bowling
and pizza nights or staff bbq’s we foster a fun, family oriented and dynamic
work environment.

** About the Role **

We're on the hunt for highly versatile technician with current technology
skillset to join the dynamic TJ Microsystems team in our Cairns office.

** Computer Network and Systems Engineer **

Ideal Candidates for this role should have 5-10 Years experience across
design, implementation, maintenance, support and troubleshooting of Microsoft
Server network environments. Experience in implementation projects,
networking, virtualisation in a managed IT services environment and equivalent
Bachelor Degree or Higher and other industry qualifications are an advantage.

You should have used RMM tools such as Labtech, Kaseya or N-Able and PSA
ticketing tools such as Connectwise or AutoTask. All qualifications are an
advantage.

But you MUST be self-motivated, have good time management skills and a
positive attitude. Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills and
fluent English are critical, as you will have constant direct contact with
clients undertaking:

  * Supporting basic and complex network types ranging from 5 to 200+ users 
  * Supporting Microsoft 365, Windows Server & Desktop Technologies & Cloud Environments 
  * Installing, configuring, testing, maintaining and optimising networks, applications, Servers and Workstations. 
  * Configuration, installation of routers, firewalls, network switches, local/network printers scanners and Wireless Access Points. 
  * Network Security analysis and design 
  * Assessing and recommending improvements on client's IT Network environments (optimising networks, system upgrades, rack tidy ups etc.) 
  * Updating and Creation of IT documentation including Disaster Recovery planning, IT Systems guidelines and procedures 
  * Design and Integration of network and IT systems including third party applications 
  * Provision of advice and strategic IT Planning for IT Infrastructure for both On premises, legacy and Cloud infrastructure 
  * Occasionally work outside of usual business hours to accommodate client support needs. 
  * As you will travel to client premises at times, a Current Australian Drivers Licence is essential. 

The role involves providing technical leadership to L2 Engineers and priority
escalation including management of critical and complex issues and
emergencies. Experience in Pre sales engineering and working with the sales
team in evaluating system design and architecture in preparation of complex
SOW documents and project proposals would be an advantage.

You will be required to plan, install, manage, and maintain the following
technologies:

  * Microsoft Server Platforms 
  * Microsoft 365, Azure, Exchange (Online & Onprem) 
  * Sophos CyberSecurity products 
  * Cisco Networking, Ubiquity Wireless products 
  * VM Ware Virtualisation Platforms 
  * Cloud Migrations 
  * Storagecraft, Veem and Synology BDR Products 
  * Lenovo, HP, Dell technologies 

** What's on Offer **

We have great opportunities for energetic, motivated individual to join a
local company that enjoys a strong marketplace presence and great
relationships within the organisation and with our clients. We offer
competitive salary rates reflective of your experience and a learning
environment with opportunities to be part of a fast growth business to help
develop your career.

We combine a family-oriented, fun-loving atmosphere with a corporate IT
philosophy to create a unique fusion you won't find elsewhere. The region
offers a unique tropical lifestyle with a beautiful blend of rainforest, reef
and a culture of paradise and tranquility that most would only dream of for
their family and or children.

If this is you, please submit your resume and cover letter now.

Please include the words ‘purple monkey dishwasher’ in your cover letter.

